author: Vyasadeva
describtion:
Om Sahana Vavatu is a mantra taken from Krishna Yajurveda Taittiriya Upanishad (2.2.2).
This is a Shanti mantra. It is a tradition to always recite this mantra before the start of yoga sessions or before classes begin in schools.
